- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper focuses on the visualization of program execution and stack traces, which are related to programming languages. 
- cs.ED (Education): The paper addresses issues in education and proposes a tool for novice programmers. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper discusses the usability of existing tools and proposes a new approach to visualization, which is related to human-computer interaction. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper may involve natural language processing in analyzing existing tools, but this is less likely than the other categories.
